<!-- ── 6. FAQ ── -->
<div class="container">
  <div class="faq-section" data-reveal>
    <h2 class="faq-section__heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    {% render 'faq-accordion', question: 'Will I still hear the full mix on stage?', answer: 'Yes. The V-filter preserves the natural frequency balance while reducing harmful peaks. Most musicians say Earasers sound more natural than wearing nothing at all.' %}
    {% render 'faq-accordion', question: 'Which filter level should I use for live concerts?', answer: 'The −19 dB Comfort filter works well for most concerts and rehearsals. For loud festivals or front-of-stage positions, choose the −26 dB Standard filter.' %}
    {% render 'faq-accordion', question: 'How do I choose my size?', answer: 'Use your earbud experience as a reference. If earbuds fall out easily, try XS or S. If they feel too tight, try M. When unsure, order the Small & Medium combo — you get both sizes and can keep the best fit.' %}
    {% render 'faq-accordion', question: 'Can I talk to bandmates without removing them?', answer: 'Yes — the open canal design lets speech through naturally. No need to remove them between songs or during soundcheck conversations.' %}
    {% render 'faq-accordion', question: 'How do I clean them?', answer: 'Rinse with warm water and mild soap. Dry completely before storing. Avoid alcohol or harsh solvents — these degrade the medical-grade silicone over time.' %}
  </div>
</div>

